Dakota Territory (1863-03-03)

1863/03/03 -> 1864/05/25

The United States created Idaho Territory from Dakota, Nebraska, and Washington Territories. Dakota Territory was reduced to the area of present North Dakota and South Dakota, plus a small area of present Nebraska.

(U.S. Stat., vol. 12, ch. 117[1863], sec. 1/p. 808; Van Zandt, 134-136, 156-157)
